Dangote to Start Sierra Leone Cement Plant by 2013, Koroma Says

-- B y   S i l a s   G b a n d i a
-- 
2011-09-02T14:11:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/dangote-to-start-sierra-leone-cement-plant-by-2013-koroma-says.html
Dangote Group  of  Nigeria  plans to
start its cement factory in  Sierra Leone  by 2013, according to
the press office of President Ernest Bai Koroma, who met Dangote
Chief Executive Officer  Aliko Dangote .  The plant will produce 500,000 metric tons of the building
material each year, the Freetown-based presidency, known as the
State House, said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Silas Gbandia in Freetown via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 